CZI awarded a grant to the OME team towards the design of a new image data format (https://forum.image.sc/t/next-generation-file-formats-for-bioimaging/31361), although it is unclear whether this involves design of general purpose interfaces to image data and metadata.

Several Python projects are working towards hardware abstraction (for instance, see: https://github.com/python-data-acquisition/meta and  https://github.com/MicronOxford/microscope), but do not support as many hardware components as µManager .
Discussing design matters in a single place (such as started here: https://github.com/python-data-acquisition/meta) will be beneficial to all.

older NI equipment - especially ensuring the equipment responds correctly to input triggers - was so problematic that Vidrio (https://vidriotechnologies.com/) - the company around the Open Source microscope acquisition platform ScanImage) is now developing its own digital/analog IO hardware.
